The following works for me without using the `file-saver` dependency. It uses the [buffer output method](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs?tab=readme-ov-file#writing-xlsx):

``` js
        file = await workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer();

        // Create a hidden link to the file
        const downloadLink = document.createElement("a");
        downloadLink.download = "excelfile.xlsx"; // File name
        downloadLink.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(
            new Blob([file], {
                type: "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet",
            })
        );
        downloadLink.style.display = "none";

        // Add the link to DOM
        document.body.appendChild(downloadLink);

        // "Click" the link
        downloadLink.click();

        // Remove the link from the DOM
        downloadLink.remove();

```
